<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="22" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="23.[192,1440,1531,1619]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,338,1531,1555]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">BIOLOGY.</emphasis>
Little is known about the biology of this species. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1847" box="[928,1217,1531,1555]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Heterogomphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eteocles">
<emphasis box="[928,1217,1531,1555]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Heterogomphus eteocles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been reported as a pest of 
<taxonomicName authority="Lindm." authorityName="Lindm." box="[328,704,1563,1587]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Chusquea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ramosissima">
<emphasis box="[328,610,1563,1587]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Chusquea ramosissima</emphasis>
Lindm.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barnhart" authorityYear="1895" baseAuthorityName="R.Br." box="[717,817,1563,1587]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
) in 
<collectingCountry box="[860,984,1563,1587]" name="Argentina" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Keller, H. A." box="[997,1142,1563,1587]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" pagination="461 - 471" refId="ref25681" refString="Keller, H. A. 2003. Mythical origin of Chusquea ramosissima (Poaceae), the ancient knife of the Guaranis. Economic Botany 57 (4): 461 - 471." type="journal article" year="2003">Keller 2003</bibRefCitation>
). In Brazilian Amazonia, adults have been collected from areas of seasonal whitewater inundation forest (várzea).
</paragraph>
